<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ871215-0144 </DOCNO><HL> Square D Closes Two Plants</HL><DD> 12/15/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> SQD </IN><DATELINE> PALATINE, Ill.  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Square D Co. said it closed two small plants that will result in a $17 million charge, equal to 59 cents a share, in the fourth quarter.    The electrical products maker said it shut its U.S. Robots unit assembly plant in Carlsbad, Calif., and a copper foil plant in Ireland as part of a continuing restructuring program. The number of workers involved in the closings wasn't disclosed.    Despite the charge, the company forecast higher profit for the year than in 1986, when it reported earnings of $98.9 million, or $3.42 a share. </TEXT></DOC>